{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pulls/1984","id":3991752888,"node_id":"PR_kwDOFkXREs7t7VC4","html_url":"https://github.com/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pull/1984","diff_url":"https://github.com/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pull/1984.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pull/1984.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/issues/1984","number":1984,"state":"closed","locked":false,"title":"Experts4bit: fused MoE weights in 4-bit NF4/FP4","user":{"login":"zaid646","id":119002999,"node_id":"U_kgDOBxfXdw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/119002999?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646","html_url":"https://github.com/zaid646","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zaid646/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\nAdds `bitsandbytes.nn.Experts4bit` — a module for storing fused Mixture-of-Experts weights (gate\\_up\\_proj + down\\_proj) in 4-bit NF4/FP4 precision. Each expert is quantized independently with per-expert absmax, and dequantized on-the-fly during the forward pass, keeping the runtime memory footprint small.\n\nCloses #1965\n\n## Motivation\n\n`transformers` v5 stores MoE expert weights as 3D tensors (e.g. `[num\\_experts, intermediate, hidden]`). `Linear4bit` cannot wrap these because it expects 2D `nn.Linear` weights. `Experts4bit` fills this gap.\n\n## Design\n\n- Plain `nn.Parameter` for packed uint8 weights\n- Per-expert float32 absmax buffers\n- `from_float()` classmethod for easy construction\n- Per-expert dequant loop\n- Gated activation (SiLU/SwiGLU) support\n- Standard `state_dict` serialization\n\n## Benchmark Results (RTX 3090)\n\n### Memory Savings\n4-bit uses ~28% of fp16 memory (72% reduction, near the 75% theoretical max).\n\n### Quantization Error (NF4)\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| MAE | 0.073 |\n| RMSE | 0.092 |\n\n### Throughput\n| Experts | Tokens/sec |\n|---------|------------|\n| 8 | ~5000 |\n| 64 | ~4000 |\n\n## Testing\n\n12 tests covering quant round-trip, shape validation, error cases, forward vs reference, and state_dict round-trip. All pass. No regressions in existing test suites.","created_at":"2026-07-04T20:37:16Z","updated_at":"2026-07-16T20:14:15Z","closed_at":"2026-07-16T18:55:16Z","merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"b0a9162de74432b5c0a77c59cb7cc3ea9ba7a05b","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[{"id":3056972036,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwzMDU2OTcyMDM2","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/labels/Duplicate","name":"Duplicate","color":"cfd3d7","default":false,"description":"This issue or pull request already exists"}],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pulls/1984/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pulls/1984/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/issues/1984/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bitsandbytes-foundation/bitsandbytes/statuses/407880efdc3e17ebb96e37d9ca357fc57bff40b3","head":{"label":"zaid646